A5.text: In April 2010, Spirit Airlines became the first U.S. airline to charge passengers for carry-on bags.

A8.text: Allegiant Air is an American low-cost airline headquartered in Las Vegas, Nevada.

A9.text: The airline focuses on serving leisure traffic from small and medium-sized cities which it considers to be underserved, using an ultra low-cost business model with minimal inclusions in fares and a greater number of add-on fees.
